Title:
LDAP BOF Collection

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- A collection of 40+ LDAP-focused Beacon Object Files (BOFs) intended to run inside C2 agents (built for Adaptix C2, but usable anywhere BOFs and argument passing are supported).  
- It addresses the need to perform Active Directory enumeration and privilege escalation actions without relying on SOCKS/proxying external tooling (e.g., ldapsearch), by executing LDAP operations directly from the compromised host context.  
- The repo implements both standard LDAP (389) with signing/sealing and LDAPS (636) with permissive certificate validation (accept-all callback).  
- It provides commands for AD object enumeration, creation, modification, deletion, ACL/DACL manipulation, delegation configuration (including RBCD), and convenience “attack macros” that chain common abuse steps.  
- Useful primarily for red teams and pentesters operating in AD environments who want low-friction, in-agent LDAP tradecraft and automation.  
- Interesting because it packages a broad set of bloodyAD-like capabilities into BOFs, including DN/username auto-detection and Adaptix AxScript command registration.

Technical Focus:
- LDAP/LDAPS binds, signing & sealing, certificate validation bypass (accept-all)
- Active Directory object enumeration and attribute operations (read/add/set/remove)
- AD security descriptors: DACL/ACE parsing and WriteDACL-style modifications
- Delegation abuse: constrained/unconstrained delegation and Resource-Based Constrained Delegation (msDS-AllowedToActOnBehalfOfOtherIdentity)
- UserAccountControl (UAC) flag manipulation and SPN management
- BOF development/integration (beacon.h-style APIs, Adaptix AxScript mappings)

Use Cases:
- Enumerate users/computers/groups, SPNs, delegation settings, and domain info via rootDSE from an implanted host
- Identify writable/modifiable AD objects and inspect ACLs to plan privilege escalation
- Add/modify ACEs to grant GenericAll/GenericWrite or DCSync-equivalent rights (where permissions allow)
- Configure RBCD or delegation settings to enable lateral movement/impersonation paths
- Create users/computers/groups and adjust attributes (SPNs, UAC flags) for roasting or persistence
- Perform sensitive operations over LDAPS when LDAP is blocked or when changing passwords/attributes

Keywords:
LDAP, LDAPS, Active Directory, BOF, Beacon Object File, Adaptix C2, AxScript, rootDSE, Distinguished Name, security descriptor, ntSecurityDescriptor, DACL, ACE, WriteDACL, GenericAll, GenericWrite, DCSync, Resource-Based Constrained Delegation, msDS-AllowedToActOnBehalfOfOtherIdentity, ServicePrincipalName, UserAccountControl, Kerberoasting, AS-REP roasting, machineAccountQuota, MinGW-w64